overview: >-
  The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic design of
  their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The
  process began with a thorough review of the existing visual elements, leading
  to the implementation of a new, calming sleep-themed color palette and custom
  utility classes. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders,
  and progress bars were enhanced with improved visual feedback and transitions.
  The main questionnaire form and intro section were redesigned with subtle
  background elements, thematic icons, and a more engaging layout.

  Throughout the process, a strong emphasis was placed on applying consistent
  styling across all 14 questionnaire sections, replacing generic gray
  backgrounds and text with theme-aligned colors and refined card-like
  groupings. After an initial review, the user highlighted inconsistencies in
  the Report section's card headers and text colors, which were subsequently
  unified to match the overall sleep theme. Additionally, a React console error
  concerning  values being passed to input components was diagnosed and
  fixed by implementing a safe value conversion in the  component. The
  outcome is a visually cohesive, professional, and aesthetically pleasing sleep
  questionnaire application.
